description: There were 44,246 individuals enrolled in TexKat in 2005. Roughly 13 percent of these enrollees had at least one ED visit during the sample period, with one quarter of these individuals having more than one visit. Across all enrollees the most common diagnosis was other upper respiratory infection, but there were significant differences in diagnosis patterns across ethnic groups. The regression analysis suggests little difference in ED utilization across genders, but significant contrasts across ethnic and age groups.
